48:15','2012-09-06 12:48:15','http://blog.fraktio.axis-of-evil.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/stripe.png','stripe.png','','inherit','open','open','','stripe-png','','','2012-09-06 12:48:15','2012-09-06 12:48:15','',0,'http://blog.fraktio.axis-of-evil.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/stripe.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(10,1,'2012-09-06 12:37:24','2012-09-06 12:37:24','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision','','','2012-09-06 12:37:24','2012-09-06 12:37:24','',1,'http://blog.fraktio.axis-of-evil.org/?p=10',0,'revision','',0),(11,1,'2012-09-06 13:01:27','2012-09-06 13:01:27','','stripe','','inherit','open','open','','stripe','','','2012-09-06 13:01:27','2012-09-06 13:01:27','',0,'http://blog.fraktio.axis-of-evil.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/stripe1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(12,1,'2012-09-06 13:02:45','2012-09-06 13:02:45','http://blog.fraktio.axis-of-evil.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/copy-912-bw2-toimistonedessa.jpg','copy-912-bw2-toimistonedessa.jpg','','inherit','open','open','','copy-912-bw2-toimistonedessa-jpg','','','2012-09-06 13:02:45','2012-09-06 13:02:45','',0,'http://blog.fraktio.axis-of-evil.org/wp-content/uploads/2012/09/copy-912-bw2-toimistonedessa.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(14,1,'2012-09-06 12:58:24','2012-09-06 12:58:24','Tää wordpress on ihan ripulia','Tussiposket','','inherit','open','open','','1-revision-2','','','2012-09-06 12:58:24','2012-09-06 12:58:24','',1,'http://swordschool.axis-of-evil.org/?p=14',0,'revision','',0),(15,1,'2012-09-17 21:01:10','2012-09-17 19:01:10','<strong>Welcome to the School</strong>\r\n\r\nIf you have never trained with us before, there are a few things you should know.\r\n\r\n1) Beginners are welcome. Every student begins knowing nothing, and we expect to teach you everything from scratch.\r\n\r\n2) Most branches run regular beginners\' courses, which might be once a week for a couple of months, or a single weekend. These are the best ways to start, but if you are only spending a limited time within reach of a branch (we get a lot of exchange students, for instance), then get in touch and start training right away.\r\n\r\n3) You will need only a white t-shirt, dark sports trousers, and indoor training shoes to start with. We can lend you the necessary equipment, such as swords and masks.\r\n\r\nContact your <a title=\"Training\" href=\"http://swordschool.dr-kobros.com/index.php/current-students/\">nearest branch</a>, or<a href=\"mailto:info@swordschool.com\"> email us</a>.\r\n\r\nThe next beginners\' course in Helsinki will run on Tuesday evenings from March 5th to April 23rd. Class runs from 1800-1930. <a title=\"Helsinki Beginners\" href=\"http://swordschool.dr-kobros.com/index.php/helsinki-beginners/\">Click here for more information and to register.</a>\r\n\r\n<strong>Age and Disability Policy</strong>\r\n\r\nSwordsmanship training is appropriate for any person who can behave as a reasonable adult. Every student should finish class healthier than they started it.\r\n\r\nOur youngest student started at age 10; our oldest started at age 58. It is uncommon for students younger than 15 years old to be emotionally and physically capable of handling our regular training, but that is not a hard and fast rule. We encourage younger students (those under 16) to bring a parent with them to watch the first class, after which the school, the parent and the child together can decide if the child is ready. We require written permission from a parent or guardian for every student who is not legally adult.\r\nThe school does not as yet run specific children\'s classes.\r\n\r\nWe have never encountered a physically perfect human being, so everybody starts out somewhere along the scale from incapacitated to super-athlete. We define ourselves by what we can do, not by what we can\'t, and it is part of the School\'s mission to expand every student\'s capabilities as far as possible. In practice, students have successfully trained with a range of physical disabilities including severe bone malformation, amputated limbs, and partial paralysis. The school expects all students, as reasonable adults, to take their physical limitations into account when training- if an exercise is unhealthy for you, don\'t do it. Students with unusually severe disabilities should make time with the instructor (in free-training sessions, or in private lessons) to work out ways to adapt the Art to their particular body.\r\nTraining at the school cannot replace medical supervision or physiotherapy. If you have any doubts, consult your doctor and the instructor before starting training.','Beginners','','publish','closed','open','','beginners','','','2013-02-01 11:46:56','2013-02-01 09:46:56','',0,'http://swordschool.axis-of-evil.org/?page_id=15',0,'page','',0),(16,1,'2012-09-17 21:00:54','2012-09-17 19:00:54','','Beginners','','inherit','open','open','','15-revision','','','2012-09-17 21:00:54','2012-09-17 19:00:54','',15,'http://swordschool.axis-of-evil.org/?p=16',0,'revision','',0),(17,1,'2012-09-17 21:01:36','2012-09-17 19:01:36','A medieval combat seminar is a lively and entertaining way to build team spirit on a corporate refreshment day, or build a thirst for a bachelor party. The content can be adjusted to suit your needs and interests, and we can organise the event for a time that suits you.\r\n\r\nIf you come to us, we can provide a safe training environment, and all necessary equipment. If you have a space available we can come to you, bringing a more limited range of weapons and protective gear.\r\n\r\nPrices and brochures available on request.\r\n\r\nContact us at info@swordschool.com','Book an Event','','publish','closed','open','','book-an-event','','','2012-11-21 14:16:59','2012-11-21 12:16:59','',0,'http://swordschool.axis-of-evil.org/?page_id=17',0,'page','',0),(18,1,'2012-09-17 21:01:25','2012-09-17 19:01:25','','Book an Event','','inherit','open','open','','17-revision','','','2012-09-17 21:01:25','2012-09-17 19:01:25','',17,'http://swordschool.axis-of-evil.org/?p=18',0,'revision','',0),(19,1,'2012-09-17 21:02:04','2012-09-17 19:02:04','<h3>Where Can I Train?</h3>\r\nThe branches of the school and affiliated organisations are listed here. The School as a whole comprises a wide range of different organisations, united by a common syllabus. The local branches have a high degree of autonomy in what and how they train- for example, some groups will follow our Fiore syllabus, but also run training in Victorian physical culture, or 18th century black-powder shooting, which is drawn from other sources. Other groups will stick purely to the School syllabus.\r\n<h3>Who can train?</h3>\r\nSwordsmanship training is appropriate for any person who can behave as a reasonable adult. Every student should finish class healthier than they started it.\r\n\r\nOur youngest student started at age 10; our oldest started at age 58. It is uncommon for students younger than 15 years old to be emotionally and physically capable of handling our regular training, but that is not a hard and fast rule. We encourage younger students (those under 16) to bring a parent with them to watch the first class, after which the school, the parent and the child together can decide if the child is ready. We require written permission from a parent or guardian for every student who is not legally adult.\r\nThe school does not as yet run specific children\'s classes.\r\n\r\nWe have never encountered a physically perfect human being, so everybody starts out somewhere along the scale from incapacitated to super-athlete. We define ourselves by what we can do, not by what we can\'t, and it is part of the School\'s mission to expand every student\'s capabilities as far as possible. In practice, students have successfully trained with a range of physical disabilities including severe bone malformation, amputated limbs, and partial paralysis. The school expects all students, as reasonable adults, to take their physical limitations into account when training- if an exercise is unhealthy for you, don\'t do it. Students with unusually severe disabilities should make time with the instructor (in free-training sessions, or in private lessons) to work out ways to adapt the Art to their particular body.\r\nTraining at the school cannot replace medical supervision or physiotherapy. If you have any doubts, consult your doctor and the instructor before starting training.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3>Classes and Events calendar</h3>\r\n[google-calendar-events id=\"1\" type=\"ajax\" title=\"Events on\" max=\"10\"]','Training','','publish','closed','open','','current-students','','','2012-12-04 11:15:50','2012-12-04 09:15:50','',0,'http://swordschool.axis-of-evil.org/?page_id=19',0,'page','',0),(20,1,'2012-09-17 21:01:52','2012-09-17 19:01:52','','Current Students','','inherit','open','open','','19-revision','','','2012-09-17 21:01:52','2012-09-17 19:01:52','',19,'http://swordschool.axis-of-evil.org/?p=20',0,'revision','',0),(21,3,'2012-12-17 11:31:41','2012-12-17 09:31:41','<strong>Welcome to the School</strong>\n\nIf you have never trained with us before, there are a few things you should know.\n\n1) Beginners are welcome. Every student begins knowing nothing, and we expect to teach you everything from scratch.\n\n2) Most branches run regular beginners\' courses, which might be once a week for a couple of months, or a single weekend. These are the best ways to start, but if you are only spending a limited time within reach of a branch (we get a lot of exchange students, for instance), then get in touch and start training right away.\n\n3) You will need only a white t-shirt, dark sports trousers, and indoor training shoes to start with. We can lend you the necessary equipment, such as swords and masks.\n\nContact your <a title=\"Training\" href=\"http://swordschool.dr-kobros.com/index.php/current-students/\">nearest branch</a>, 